sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K216005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: PyeaR promoter, responsive to nitrate, nitrite and nitric oxide
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: BioBricked from E. coli K-12 genomic DNA by the Edinburgh 2009 iGEM team.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: PyeaR promoter. This is the promoter of the Escherichia coli yeaR/yoaG operon (see Lin, H.-Y., Bledsoe, P.J., and Stewart, V. 2007. Activation of yeaR-yoaG operon transcription by the nitrate-responsive regulator NarL is independent of oxygen-responsive regulator Fnr in ''Escherichia coli'' K-12. J. Bacteriol. 189, 7539-7548). Unlike other E. coli promoters responding to nitrate and nitrite, this promoter is not repressed under aerobic conditions.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edinburgh iGEM 2009

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K274370
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: PoPS -> P2 ogr - PF promoter -> PoPS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vivian Mullin

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mRFP1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: **highly** engineered mutant of red fluorescent protein from Discosoma striata (coral)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Campbell et al., PNAS v99 p7877 URL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: monomeric RFP: Red Fluorescent Protein. Excitation peak: 584 nm Emission peak: 607 nm
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
TAATAA double stop codon added (DE).
Four silent mutations made to remove three EcoRI sites and one PstI site: A28G, A76G, A349G, G337A.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Strong RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("orig" in figure 4-14 of Ron Weiss thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I746350
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: plasmid DNA supplied by Prof. Richard Calendar, University of California.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The ogr activator taken from P2 phage acts on a class of inducible promoters (parts I746360 to I746365), inducing their activity to varying degrees. The part sequence does already contain a ribosome binding site (B0034)!
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The part does contain a RBS (B0034) already.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stefan Milde

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B1006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: modified E. coli thr terminator, replaced all A-T pairs in stem with C-G pairs
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Artificial terminator, estimated %T~>90% *8bp stem, 6nt loop *Bidirectional, estimated reverse %T~>90%
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Bidirectional, with the reverse estimated to be less effective than the forward. Has a polyA tail of 9 residues.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Haiyao Huang

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I746360
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The original source is the P2 phage genome. For our work the DNA came from plasmids, kindly supplied to us by Prof. Calendar, University of California (Berkeley): Bacteriophage PSP3 and fR73 Activator Proteins: Analysis of Promoter Specificities; Julien and Calendar, 1996; JOURNAL OF BACTERIOLOGY, Oct. 1996, p. 5668???5675
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the PF promoter taken from the P2 phage genome. It is an inducible promoter that is activated by a class of activators, including P2 ogr (I746350), PSP3 pag (I746351) and phiR73 delta (I746352). These different activators should cause different levels of activity of the PF promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stefan Milde
